intro.bodyMarkdown:
Java is statically typed: each variable has a type. Local variables often use explicit types or `var` (Java 10+).

```java
int score = 10;
String name = "Asha";
```

Behavior lives in **methods**. `main` is a common entry point.

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("go");
}
```
